title: PAULĖ
text:
About
Born and raised in Los Angeles, I spent a significant amount of my free time poring over taxi cab maps during car rides and exploring Google Earth at home. I find joy in working with maps to unravel geographical complexities and uncover hidden patterns.
Passionate about music, especially in the alternative and punk/rock genres? So am I! I’m on a (side) mission to create a radio station that celebrates the raw energy and creativity of underground music scenes.
If you have any advice, insights, or input on creating and establishing a radio station, I’d love to hear from you! Let’s collaborate to bring the sounds of indie bands and underground artists to the airwaves. Drop me a line at pauledargyte@gmail.com and let’s make some waves together!

text:
Here are some visualizations of the age variable from the centenarians dataset:


Rows: 200 Columns: 8
── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: ","
chr  (4): name, place_of_death_or_residence, gender, still_alive
dbl  (2): rank, age
date (2): birth_date, death_date

ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.






Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.3.2












library(ggplot2)

# Boxplot of age by gender
ggplot(centenarians, aes(x = gender, y = age, fill = gender)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title = "Boxplot of Age by Gender",
       x = "Gender",
       y = "Age",
       fill = "Gender")



# Boxplot of age by location
ggplot(centenarians, aes(x = place_of_death_or_residence, y = age, fill = gender)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title = "Boxplot of Age by Location",
       x = "Location",
       y = "Age",
       fill = "Gender") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))  # Rotate labels by 45 degrees
